cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.CL 

This paper is about using machine learning techniques to learn game-semantic models of programming languages. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also mentions the use of long short-term memory neural nets (LSTM), which is a popular technique in natural language processing, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves measuring accuracy and performance, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) respectively.
